Senate Resolution 413
By: Senators Kennedy of the 18th and Walker III of the 20th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life of Sergeant Patrick Michael Sondron and dedicating a bridge in his
2 memory; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, born on July 21, 1975, in Miami, Florida, Patrick Michael Sondron was the
4 cherished son of Michael and Patricia Sondron; and
5 WHEREAS, following his graduation from Orange Park High School in 1993, Sergeant
6 Sondron enlisted in the United States Air Force, where he served as a guardian of this
7 nation's freedom and liberty; and
8 WHEREAS, he continued to serve his community through a career in law enforcement,
9 starting his career in 1999 with the Fort Valley Police Department, adeptly serving on the
10 Byron Police Department, and dedicating 13 years to the Peach County Sheriff's Office,
11 where he was a sergeant for the patrol division and a member of the SWAT team; and
12 WHEREAS, Sergeant Sondron was highly regarded by the citizens of his community and
13 state and by local government officials as a person of unquestioned integrity and dedication
14 to the sound principles of law enforcement; and
