15 WHEREAS, a dedicated public servant, a respected partner in law enforcement, and a kind,
16 level-headed individual, Sergeant Sondron had a profound impact on the Warner Robins
17 community, and his loss deeply affected the citizens of Peach County; and
18 WHEREAS, Sergeant Sondron exhibited extraordinary devotion to public service,
19 outstanding loyalty, fine leadership, and meticulous attention to detail in all of his duties, and
20 it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable and distinguished Georgian be
21 recognized appropriately by dedicating a bridge in his memory.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
23 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the bridge on State Route 49 over Interstate 75 (Exit 149)
24 in Peach County is dedicated as the Sgt. Patrick Sondron Memorial Bridge.
25 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation is authorized and
26 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the Sgt. Patrick Sondron
27 Memorial Bridge.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
29 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
30 Sergeant Patrick Michael Sondron and to the Department of Transportation.
